00:46:36.770 --> 00:46:39.363
but they don't learn really
the proper, you know,

00:46:40.570 --> 00:46:41.980
tool length and that sort of thing

00:46:41.980 --> 00:46:44.070
until they get to be about four.

00:46:44.070 --> 00:46:46.138
So she gets a little frustrated too.

00:46:46.138 --> 00:46:48.260
(audience laughing)

00:46:48.260 --> 00:46:51.161
All right, enough fun, I guess.

00:46:51.161 --> 00:46:51.994
(clears throat)

00:46:51.994 --> 00:46:55.740
So, in terms of our results so far, um...

00:46:55.740 --> 00:46:58.700
I apologize because in your
abstract I put over 500,

00:46:58.700 --> 00:47:02.400
I was sure that we would
hit the 500 mark this year.

00:47:02.400 --> 00:47:04.646
499, I just can't believe it.

00:47:04.646 --> 00:47:05.640
(audience laughs)

00:47:05.640 --> 00:47:07.830
But we have 499 hunting records,

00:47:07.830 --> 00:47:09.540
those aren't all successes

00:47:09.540 --> 00:47:11.820
and that's including adults and immatures.

00:47:11.820 --> 00:47:14.330
We've only seen adolescent
and adult individuals

00:47:14.330 --> 00:47:17.040
successful in this type
of hunting behavior.

00:47:17.040 --> 00:47:19.050
Like I said, infants begin to exhibit it

00:47:19.050 --> 00:47:20.870
and they do really good
as far as making the tool

00:47:20.870 --> 00:47:22.620
but they don't make a proper tool

00:47:22.620 --> 00:47:24.960
until they get to be a juvenile.

00:47:24.960 --> 00:47:28.160
So we see about 32 hunts
per year on average

00:47:28.160 --> 00:47:30.090
when you take into account
that there are some days

00:47:30.090 --> 00:47:31.610
that we can't be there,
the river's too high

00:47:31.610 --> 00:47:32.870
or someone's sick.

00:47:32.870 --> 00:47:36.800
We think that they probably
hunt at least 50 times a year.

00:47:36.800 --> 00:47:39.570
And, again, our most
recent analysis suggest

00:47:39.570 --> 00:47:42.220
that females do hunt
significantly more than expected

00:47:42.220 --> 00:47:45.460
with tools, even though males also hunt.

00:47:45.460 --> 00:47:48.610
And we did analysis taking into account

00:47:48.610 --> 00:47:51.730
not only their membership
in the community as a whole

00:47:51.730 --> 00:47:54.730
but also their membership
and so-called hunting parties

00:47:54.730 --> 00:47:57.763
or parties that the chimpanzees
are in on those days.

00:47:59.070 --> 00:48:00.260
So, I want to talk a little bit more

00:48:00.260 --> 00:48:03.587
about just the hunters themselves,

00:48:03.587 --> 00:48:05.750
and this is a lot of color there,

00:48:05.750 --> 00:48:09.500
but I wanted to show you the
top 10 hunters at Fongoli

00:48:09.500 --> 00:48:11.660
and also the different types of foods

00:48:11.660 --> 00:48:13.600
or prey that they hunt.

00:48:13.600 --> 00:48:17.120
And so, you have two
females that are actually

00:48:17.120 --> 00:48:19.520
among the top 10 hunters at Fongoli.

00:48:19.520 --> 00:48:22.360
Interestingly, I think is
that both of those females,

00:48:22.360 --> 00:48:24.010
females are very high-ranking.

00:48:24.010 --> 00:48:27.000
So Tumbo there is currently
our alpha female based

00:48:27.000 --> 00:48:29.990
on these very stylized pant grunt records,

00:48:29.990 --> 00:48:33.010
sorry, vocalizations, and we keep records

00:48:33.010 --> 00:48:35.410
of these vocalizations where
a subordinate individual

00:48:35.410 --> 00:48:37.970
will pant, grunt to a dominant individual.

00:48:37.970 --> 00:48:40.900
And Tumbo actually overtook
that alpha position

00:48:40.900 --> 00:48:44.480
from Farafa there about two years ago.

00:48:44.480 --> 00:48:48.440
And so, females actually do
hunt some in this community

00:48:48.440 --> 00:48:50.180
or at least enough to be considered

00:48:50.180 --> 00:48:52.620
among the top 10 Fongoli hunters.

00:48:52.620 --> 00:48:56.580
And also I'd like to point out
that we have a tie right now

00:48:56.580 --> 00:48:59.130
for the very top hunter,
and one is the alpha male,

00:48:59.130 --> 00:49:00.053
that's David.

00:49:01.090 --> 00:49:05.040
He is tied for the top
hunting position with Siberut

00:49:05.040 --> 00:49:07.930
and some of you will be
happy to know that Siberut

00:49:07.930 --> 00:49:11.100
who is pictured there is
not only the oldest hunter

00:49:11.100 --> 00:49:12.580
in the group, he's oldest male,

00:49:12.580 --> 00:49:15.023
but he's also the lowest
ranking male as well.

00:49:16.170 --> 00:49:19.250
And then if you look at female
hunting behavior in general,

00:49:19.250 --> 00:49:21.510
females, almost all females hunt

00:49:21.510 --> 00:49:23.350
and almost all males hunt as well,

00:49:23.350 --> 00:49:25.160
so they hunt about what you would expect

00:49:25.160 --> 00:49:27.670
or at least their participation
in hunting overall

00:49:27.670 --> 00:49:30.340
is what you would expect based
on their their membership

00:49:30.340 --> 00:49:32.583
in the Fongoli community.

00:49:35.320 --> 00:49:38.480
I wanted to look, talk a little
bit about Fongoli hunting

00:49:40.772 --> 00:49:44.670
and the context of female
hunting across study sites.

00:49:44.670 --> 00:49:46.160
So, Ian talked about that some

00:49:46.160 --> 00:49:49.990
and I've used data from
his work and others

00:49:49.990 --> 00:49:53.600
to look at Fongoli female
hunting and, in fact,

00:49:53.600 --> 00:49:55.700
there are females
elsewhere that also engage

00:49:55.700 --> 00:49:56.670
in quite a bit of hunting.

00:49:56.670 --> 00:49:59.300
In fact, females at
Mahale hunt a little more

00:49:59.300 --> 00:50:01.020
than females at Fongoli if you look

00:50:01.020 --> 00:50:04.350
at Fongoli female
hunting behavior overall.

00:50:04.350 --> 00:50:06.260
And then when you look at tool use,

00:50:06.260 --> 00:50:09.770
you see that Fongoli
females do hunt quite a bit,

00:50:09.770 --> 00:50:12.070
almost half of the tool-assisted hunting

00:50:12.070 --> 00:50:13.470
at Fongoli is by females.

00:50:13.470 --> 00:50:17.490
And, again, remember that we
have fewer females at Fongoli,

00:50:17.490 --> 00:50:20.690
we don't follow females
systematically like we do males.

00:50:20.690 --> 00:50:23.920
And so one question as to why females hunt

00:50:23.920 --> 00:50:26.503
is basically as David started out with,

00:50:27.600 --> 00:50:28.810
you know, it's probably no surprise

00:50:28.810 --> 00:50:32.750
that the chimps gained a lot
of nutrition from hunting,

00:50:32.750 --> 00:50:35.350
but I think perhaps a
more interesting question

00:50:35.350 --> 00:50:38.060
is why females don't
hunt more at other sites.

00:50:38.060 --> 00:50:40.990
And Ian talked about some
of these issues as well

00:50:40.990 --> 00:50:43.510
that I'll pursue right now.

00:50:43.510 --> 00:50:46.143
And so, if you looked
at for example theft,

00:50:47.860 --> 00:50:49.960
there's not a lot of theft at Fongoli,

00:50:49.960 --> 00:50:52.790
so when I use the word share
I'm referring to, basically,

00:50:52.790 --> 00:50:55.740
the last three categories I
think that David talked about.

00:50:55.740 --> 00:51:00.470
So active food transfer
but not theft, right,

00:51:00.470 --> 00:51:02.440
and passive food transfer, et cetera.

00:51:02.440 --> 00:51:05.150
So I consider theft to
be a different category

00:51:05.150 --> 00:51:07.360
and at Fongoli you have very little theft.

00:51:07.360 --> 00:51:10.370
The only thought we've seen involves

00:51:10.370 --> 00:51:13.420
two different alpha males,
so very little theft.

00:51:13.420 --> 00:51:16.000
Whereas at other sites you
do have quite a bit of theft

00:51:16.000 --> 00:51:18.913
and so I believe, as Ian said,

00:51:20.600 --> 00:51:23.750
females don't have incentive
to hunt at some sites.

00:51:23.750 --> 00:51:26.040
At Fongoli there definitely is incentive

00:51:26.040 --> 00:51:30.750
and not only females, but this
is a little video of, again,

00:51:30.750 --> 00:51:32.660
that lower-ranking male.

00:51:32.660 --> 00:51:34.810
So out of 13 males he's number 13.

00:51:34.810 --> 00:51:36.850
He's the oldest male, that's Siberut.

00:51:36.850 --> 00:51:39.960
So he's walking by a number of adult males

00:51:39.960 --> 00:51:42.360
with this bushbuck fawn that he's captured

00:51:42.360 --> 00:51:46.090
and no one makes any
attempt to take it from him.

00:51:46.090 --> 00:51:48.590
He had actually been eating
on that fawn for over an hour

00:51:48.590 --> 00:51:50.740
and he had a number of
individuals sitting around

00:51:50.740 --> 00:51:53.350
basically begging, he
didn't share with them.

00:51:53.350 --> 00:51:55.050
And as he moves off you'll see

00:51:55.050 --> 00:51:57.640
that there's another older
male that will follow him

00:51:57.640 --> 00:51:59.333
and this is his ally, Bandit.

00:52:04.470 --> 00:52:06.080
Where's Bandit?

00:52:06.080 --> 00:52:07.800
There he is.

00:52:07.800 --> 00:52:09.690
Calmly following his buddy Siberut out.

00:52:09.690 --> 00:52:12.830
And so, he did end up sharing with Bandit.

00:52:12.830 --> 00:52:17.830
So not only do you see
some sort of concept...

00:52:18.750 --> 00:52:20.230
Well, I hate to say concept of ownership

00:52:20.230 --> 00:52:21.130
but you see tolerance.

00:52:21.130 --> 00:52:24.740
So tolerance of possession of prey, uh...

00:52:25.720 --> 00:52:28.020
By dominant males of these
low ranking individuals,

00:52:28.020 --> 00:52:30.050
females and also lower ranking males.

00:52:30.050 --> 00:52:32.030
So I think that at
Fongoli you actually have

00:52:32.030 --> 00:52:33.030
the incentive to hunt.

00:52:33.030 --> 00:52:35.880
It's one of the reasons that
you see so much hunting,

00:52:35.880 --> 00:52:38.253
at least tool-assisted hunting in females.

00:52:39.140 --> 00:52:41.010
I wanna show it a slightly different way.

00:52:41.010 --> 00:52:43.540
So, these are the same top 10 hunters,

00:52:43.540 --> 00:52:47.100
but rather than being
expressed in the number of prey

00:52:47.100 --> 00:52:50.160
that they brought in, this
is the number of kilograms

00:52:50.160 --> 00:52:52.660
or estimated kilograms of meat, right?

00:52:52.660 --> 00:52:54.800
And so, you see that David has jumped up

